					I actually have a friend who is part of the PHP development mailling list and he was one of the programmers who voted for the deprecation of the mysql_* library.<br />I think that is really good - all mysql_* should be removed because they pose a security risk.<br /><span  style='font-size: 14px'>And I don&#39;t get why people use mysqli - PDO is way more updated and secure. </span><br />I wish there was way people would start learning making SQL queries using at least mysqli or even better PDO. Most of the beginners start with mysql_* functions and that is just plain wrong...
					
